blog.title: Well that's strange!
blog.description:
Welcome!  I create, using the all-mighty classic Microsoft XP Paint, my own pokemon fusions. All the sprites come from pokestadium and usually people on deviantart/ the xy/sun&moon sprite project. I don't own any of the sprite used, I just fuse them! 
REQUESTS ARE OPEN! Ask Box: 3/15.
PLEASE FEEL FREE TO DRAW MY FUSIONS!!  I absolutely love it when people draw them! There's no need to ask either! Just make sure you tag me so them I can see it!
I hope you enjoy my fusions!

summary: Volcazor Volcarona and Scizor fusion Bug/Fire Type Ability: Bulletproof Stats: HP - 90, Atk - 120, Def - 100, SpA - 120, SpD -...
caption:
Volcazor

Volcarona and Scizor fusion

Bug/Fire Type

Ability: Bulletproof

Stats: HP - 90, Atk - 120, Def - 100, SpA - 120, SpD - 100, Spe - 105

The Volcano Claws Pokemon

Volcazor’s claws constantly spew fire from them and the inside is filled with lava.  Its body is actually as hard as steel and can absorb impacts like they’re nothing.  It’s wings both regulate its temperature and spew embers as it flies.

Request for anon.  I hope you like it!

summary: Jayafly (juh-eye-uh-flye) Very much like a butterfly, except for two pretty major exceptions.  Firstly, the Jayafly is huge,...
caption:
Jayafly (juh-eye-uh-flye)

Very much like a butterfly, except for two pretty major exceptions.  Firstly, the Jayafly is huge, which makes it very difficult to hide.  Secondly, and maybe because of its inability to hide, it has an electrified antenna on top of its head, granting it somewhat of a force field against any sort of attack, and a light attack against opponents.  Its main attack however, uses the grip of its tentacles to grab onto its opponent, who then has to deal with that electric buzz, often resulting in a numbing sensation or even a seizure.

Created through the Paper app, using my fingers on an iPhone.

/pao.
